text: Saïd Bouhadja (22 April 1938 - 25 November 2020) was an Algerian politician. He was a member of the National Liberation Front. He was born in Skikda, Algeria. From 2017 until his death, he was a member of the People's National Assembly from 2017 until his death. He was the president of the assembly from 2017 until 2018. He unsuccessfully ran for President of Algeria in 2019. Bouhadja died on 25 November 2020 in Algiers, aged 82.Décès de l’ancien président de l’APN Saïd Bouhadja ==References== Category:1938 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Algerian politicians
